<dl id="s14042ad"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us14" href="#s14042ad">Oxen of the Sun: </a><a href="../../FF/unbs/s14all.htm#s14042ad">sector 42(ad)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> reasons good &amp; cogent <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="s14042ad"><li>Ulysses </li><li><a href="../../ulex/p/lexp.htm#s14042ad">2021</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/p/p86.htm#s14042ad">2017</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/p/p86.htm#s14042ad">1986 (14.1278f)</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/p/l22p.htm#s14042ad">1922</a> </li><li><ms href="#s14042ad">MS NLI.11E-6</ms> </li><li><a name="p12d" href="../udra/u14da.htm#p12d">Usage</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/p/p12d.htm#s14042ad">Draft: 14.2</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">The worst fault which divines and the doctors of the Sorbonne can allege against it, is, that if there is but a capful of wind in or about Paris, &apos;tis more blasphemously &ldquo;<i>Sacre Dieu&apos;d</i>&rdquo; there, than in any other aperture of the whole city; and with <mark>reason good and cogent</mark>, messieurs,&mdash;for it comes against you without crying &ldquo;<i>Garde d&apos;eau;</i>&rdquo; and with such unpremeditated puffs, that, of the few who cross it with their hats on, not one in fifty but hazards two livres and a half, which is its full worth. <small> Laurence Sterne, <a name="LSAS" href="/udra/udex.htm#LSAS"><cite title="source">A Sentimental Journey</cite></a> (1888), 236f</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also <a name="un5007q" href="un5all.htm#un5007q">UN5 (NLI.5B):007(q)</a> for <cite>UG</cite> 14.706, and <a name="s14082j" href="s14all.htm#s14082j">Sheet 14.082(j)</a>. </mm> </dd></dl>
